alert.note: Alert for East Puget Sound Lowlands (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued December 22 at 12:34PM PST until December 23 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 PM PST THIS EVENING... ...WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 7 PM PST FRIDAY... * WHAT...For the Winter Storm Warning, heavy mixed precipitation expected. Total snow accumulations of up to two inches and ice accumulations of one tenth to one quarter of an inch. Winds gusting as high as 50 mph. For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills. Wind chills as low as zero. * WHERE...East Puget Sound Lowlands from Snohomish County to Pierce County, including Arlington, Gold Bar, Duvall, Snoqualmie, Buckley, and Eatonville. * WHEN...For the Winter Storm Warning, from 4 PM this afternoon to 7 PM PST Friday. For the Wind Chill Advisory, until 10 PM PST this evening. * IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Coldest areas will occur nearest the gaps in the Cascades, especially along the I-90 and US-2 corridors. This is will be a complex mix of winter precipitation with potentially significant impacts.
info.instruction: If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in your vehicle in case of an emergency. Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a hat, and gloves. For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.
